Since updating to Jira Agile 6.4.2 I can no longer reorder issues in the Plan view. After each attempt the following message and shown and the previous order is restored

{quote}
JIRA Agile cannot execute the rank operation. This board has recently been configured to use the Rank field. The system must be re-indexed before you can rank issues. Ask your administrator to perform a manual re-index.
{quote}

I have already executed a manual re-index as suggested, but it did not solve the problem.

I cannot find any useful information in the logs when reproducing the error.

We are receiving the following error when we try to clone any issue in our JIRA:

{noformat}
Exception: com.atlassian.activeobjects.internal.ActiveObjectsSqlException: There was a SQL exception thrown by the Active Objects library: Database: - name:PostgreSQL - version:8.4.8 - minor version:4 - major version:8 Driver: - name:PostgreSQL Native Driver - version:PostgreSQL 8.4 JDBC4 (build 702) org.postgresql.util.PSQLException: ERROR: column "DEFAULT_LANE" cannot be cast to type boolean
{noformat}


There seems to be no difference if we try to clone with/without attachments or links.

We are using version v6.3-OD-08-005-WN. Hopefully you can see it from my account, if not, tell me and I will give you our ID.

h3. Steps to Replicate the Problem:
# Install JIRA;
# Install JIRA Agile;
# Create the *Demonstration Project*;
# Create a new Scrum Board for the DEMO project;
# Add a Sprint in this board;
# Add DEMO-1 to this sprint;
# Open the issue DEMO-1 in JIRA;
# Right-click "View on Board" and select "Open in new Tab".

h3. Expected Behavior
The board would load in the new tab, as it is loaded when clicking directly on "View on Board".

h3. Actual Behavior
JIRA cannot resolve the URL correctly, and therefore JIRA only displays its header and footer. 

h4. Note
The problem seem to be the last part of the URL when opening on a new tab. If the complete URL is:
{noformat:borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#6A8EB3 |bgColor=#F8F8F8}
http://ecrmac-05:8080/jira627/secure/GHGoToBoard.jspa?issueId=10000&inline=true
{noformat}
Removing the {{&inline=true}} from the URL in the new tab will cause the board to be displayed correctly.

This is a regression of GHS-8630, but it can be reproduced on JIRA Agile 6.3.13.1 as well.

During Creation of new issues and updating existing issues response time is unacceptable. 

When accessing epics the following message is received;
